@node install " Installation"

@{b}Installation
************@{ub}

    Please use the install script. Installing by hand is so complicated!

@endnode

@node mainwin " Main window"

@{b}Main window
***********@{ub}

    Main window contains two important part: The source and destination
document.

    You have to load the foreign languaged text into source, what you want
to translate. If you doubleclick on a word, the program tries to search for
that in the given dictionaries.

    In destination document, you can edit the translated text. Using
texteditor.mcc can be found in MUI settings.

    To active a document, use tab! There is four hotkeys to dispose and add
documents to the window:

    "F1" - removes source document

    "F2" - adds source document

    "F3" - removes destination document

    "F4" - adds destination document

@endnode

@node findword " Searching for words"

@{b}Searching for words
*******************@{ub}

    As in v1.x, there's two ways to find a word in dictionaries. If you
doubleclick on a word in source document the program tries to find it in
databases. There is one change in second way. As you can see the wordfinder
disappeared. You can find it in dictionary window. Hotkey of the menu
didn't changed. 

@endnode

@node menus " Menus"

@{b}Menus
*****@{ub}

   @{" Project    " link menu_project} - File handling and program informations
   @{" Edit       " link menu_edit} - Editing documents
   @{" Amigaguide " link menu_amigaguide} - Editing Amigaguide
   @{" Settings   " link menu_settings} - Settings of program
   @{" Extras     " link menu_extras} - Other functions

