@node menu_project " Menus - Project"

@{b}Project menu
************@{ub}

@{b}Open source...@{ub} @{fg shine}O@{fg text}
    Loads a text file to the source document.

@{b}Open Destination...@{ub} @{fg shine}L@{fg text}
    Loads a text file to destination document.

@{b}Save Destination...@{ub} @{fg shine}S@{fg text}
    Saves the contents of destination document.

@{b}Save Destination... (XPK)@{ub}
    Saves an XPK compressed file. The program uses packing method what you've already
set in XPKMasterPrefs.

@{b}About...@{ub} @{fg shine}?@{fg text}
    Some informations about the program.

@{b}About MUI...@{ub}
    Informations about Magic User Interface

@endnode

@node menu_edit " Edit menu"

@{b}Edit menu
*********@{ub}

@{b}Cut@{ub} @{fg shine}X@{fg text}
    Cuts the maked are to clipboard.

@{b}Copy@{ub} @{fg shine}C@{fg text}
    Copies the marked are to the clipboard.

@{b}Paste@{ub} @{fg shine}V@{fg text}
    Inserts the contents of clipboard to cursor position.

@{b}Find...@{ub} @{fg shine}F@{fg text}
    You can give a string to search in the active document. If you press
"Ok" button, it starts to search from cursor position. If you press
"FromTop" button, it starts to search from the beginning of the document.

@{b}Find Next@{ub} @{fg shine}N@{fg text}
    If you give a string in Find window you can continue to search for that
from cursor position. Of course in active document.

@{b}Clear Source@{ub} @{fg shine}E@{fg text}
    Clears the source document.

@{b}Clear Destination@{ub} @{fg shine}M@{fg text}
    Clears the destination document.

@endnode

@node menu_amigaguide " Amigaguide menu"

@{b}Amigaguide menu
***************@{ub}

@{b}New Guide...@{ub} @{fg shine}1@{fg text}
    Creates the header informations of an amigaguide document. In the
opened window, you have to fill all strings!
    @{i}Database @{ui}- Name of document
    @{i}Author @{ui}- Author of document
    @{i}(c) @{ui}- Copyright informations
    @{i}$VER @{ui}- Version string for the document

@{b}New Node...@{ub} @{fg shine}2@{fg text}
    Creates a new amigaguide node. As you read above, you have to fill all
strings!
    @{i}Node name @{ui}- name of the node (it's important for links)
    @{i}Node Title @{ui}- Title of the node. You can read this in the window title

@{b}Commands...@{ub} @{fg shine}3@{fg text}
    You can find the text formatting tags for amigaguide documents as a
list. If you doubleclick on one of the entries the program puts the tags
before and behind of marked area! The program creates the list from
Ltools:Prefs/agcom.prefs file what you can edit in settings/AG commands.

@{b}Link...@{ub} @{fg shine}4@{fg text}
    Link to nodes are the basical elements of an amigaguide document. You
can navigate with simple buttons in nodes. The maked text will be the
button and it points the given name of the node.

@{b}Node list...@{ub} @{fg shine}5@{fg text}
    List of nodes you created. You can append it by addign a new node to
the document, or load an amigaguide document. You can delete a selected
entry by "Delete" button.

@{b}Preview@{ub} @{fg shine}I@{fg text}
    You can see the document what you edit.

@endnode

@node menu_settings " Settings menu"

@{b}Settings menu
*************@{ub}

@{b}Dictionary, Search@{ub} @{fg shine}D@{fg text}
    You can set some atrributes in dictionary and searching. There is two
cycle gadget. One for Language Tools dictionary list and one for
LSDictionary list what you use. You can edit this list in menu
Settings/Program/Dictionaries.
    @{u}Search:@{uu} You can set by checkmarks the database to search in.
When you set Recursive the program cuts cuntinually the last letter of the
word and starts the searching again.

@{b}Program...@{ub} @{fg shine}P@{fg text}
    @{u}Program:@{uu} You can set the path of source documents and the
translated texts. In other string you can set wordwrap for texteditor.
    @{u}Dictionary paths:@{uu} The path of dictionaries. Basically they are
in the previously given place Ltools:dics. You have to set the path of
original and user dictionaries. Be careful when you use Language Tools
dictionaries. These databases are in subdirectories in Ltools:dics. For
example if you use English-German dictionaries the dictype will be "engger"
and the dictionaries will be at Ltools:dics/engger/ path. If you have some
problem see Error list window to find the bug.
    @{u}Dictionaries:@{uu} You can create the list of used dictionaries.
Name is the name of dictionary. FileID contains the codes of languages. For
example: English-Hungarian becomes to enghun. LSDictonary FileIDs can be
found in the program. FileID is the name of file without extension.
    @{u}AG Commands:@{uu} You can edit the list of amigaguide commands,
what are in the Commands window. You have to set its name, tag before
(start) and behind (end).

@{b}MUI...@{ub}
    MUI settings of the program.

@endnode

@node menu_extras " Extras menu"

@{b}Extras menu
***********@{ub}

@{b}Dictionary...@{ub} @{fg shine}W@{fg text}
    Opens the dictionary window, what contains the word search for, its
sense and a stringobject , where you can type a string to search for.

@{b}Run ARexx...@{ub}
    Runs a selected arexx macro.

@{b}Error list...@{ub} @{fg shine}J@{fg text}
    Sometimes errors occur, when you didn't set the path for dictionaries.
In this case the program informs you it cannot open the files. So... you
can see why it cannot find a word when that is in the dictionary. Maybe the
dictionaries are in wrong path. If you press "Delete" button then all
entries will be deleted.

@endnode

@node arexx " ARexx commands"

@{b}ARexx commands
**************@{ub}

    The greatest improved thing in version 2.0 is the arexx interface for
Language Tools. If you have any good idea, I will add to the program. The
port of executed Langauge Tools is 'LAMGTOOLS2.1'.

    @{b}CLEARS@{ub} - clears source document

    @{b}CLEARD@{ub} - clears destination document

    @{b}LTOOLSON@{ub} - turns on the checkmark Langauge Tools in dictionary,
search settings window

    @{b}LTOOLSOFF@{ub} - turns off the above mentioned checkmark

    @{b}LSDICON@{ub} - turns on the checkmark LSDictionary in dictionary, search
settings window

    @{b}LSDICOFF@{ub} - turns off the above mentioned checkmark

    @{b}RECON@{ub} - turns on the checkmark Recirsive in the dictionary, search
settings window

    @{b}RECOFF@{ub} - turns off the above mentioned checkmark

    @{b}CLOSEWIMAIN@{ub} - closes the main window

    @{b}OPENWIMAIN@{ub} - opens the main window

    @{b}OPENWIDIC@{ub} - opens the dictionary window

    @{b}CLOSEWIDIC@{ub} - closes the dictionary window

    @{b}FINDWORD "WORD/A"@{ub} - searches for the word given in argument

    @{b}LOADS "FILENAME/A"@{ub} - loads the file given in argument to source
document

    @{b}LOADD "FILENAME/A"@{ub} - loads the file given in argument to destination
document

    @{b}SAVED "FIELNAME/A"@{ub} - saves the contents of destination into the file
given in argument

    @{b}GETSENSE "FIELNAME/A"@{ub} - saves the contents of dictionary window into
the file given in argument

    @{b}SETSCREEN "SCREENNAME/A"@{ub} - moves the dictionary and dictionary, search
window to the screen you set
    
    @{b}PUTTAGS "FTAG/A,STAG/A"@{ub} - puts the tags the marked area before and behind

    @{b}PUTTEXT "TEXT/A"@{ub} - puts the given text into cursor position
@endnode

@node langcode " Language Codes"

@{b}Language codes
**************@{ub}
    
    FileID of Langauge Tools dictionaries contains the two language codes.
For example: FileID of Italian-English will be itaeng.

    hun - hungarian
    eng - english
    fra - french
    esp - spanish
    ita - italian
    por - portugese
    ger - german
    nor - norwegian
    swe - swedish
    rus - russian
@endnode

